# Class Features

## Ancestry and Background
In addition to what you get from your class at 1st level, you have the benefits of your selected ancestry and background.

## Initial Proficiencies
At 1st level, you gain a number of proficiencies that represent your basic training. These proficiencies are noted at the start of this class.

## Threadcraft
At 1st level, you can create supernatural threads as environmental hazards. They are visible, physical lines of reinforced thread stretched taut between two anchors. Threads do not block movement, line of effect, or line of sight. Instead, they impose consequences when a creature enters a square they occupy.

Unless otherwise stated, threads can only be anchored to **squares, terrain features, or unattended objects**. Anchoring threads to creatures requires a Weaving Style or feat.

|

### Thread Limits

You can maintain a number of threads equal to **1 plus your proficiency bonus in your Combat Seamstress class DC**.

A single thread cannot exceed **30 feet per proficiency rank** in your Combat Seamstress class DC.

Threads persist until severed or until you make your next daily preparations.

