19–20 | Legendary | 9 | 120 feet | 18th | 9

### Thread Effects

Each thread has **one effect slot**, chosen when the thread is created.

When a creature enters a square occupied by a thread during its own movement, the thread’s effect triggers. A thread can trigger only **once per creature per movement** unless an ability states otherwise.

The effects available to you are granted by class features and feats and typically impose conditions, movement penalties, or positional hindrances.

If you have an ability that allows you to exempt allies, you designate exempt creatures when you create a thread. Your exemption limit follows the standard progression for your proficiency (typically **1 plus your proficiency bonus in your Combat Seamstress class DC**). Any feats or abilities that modify or add to this limit apply. Exempt creatures do not trigger that thread’s effects, nor do they pay any action costs imposed by it.

