## Tailor's Cut
When you critically hit with your tailor scissors, the target takes 1d4 persistent bleed damage. This damage die increases to 1d6 at 5th level, 1d8 at 11th level, and 1d10 at 17th level.

## Skill Feats 2nd
At 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a skill feat.

## Combat Seamstress Feats 2nd
At 2nd level and every even-numbered level thereafter, you gain a Combat Seamstress class feat.

## Tailored Defenses 2nd

Beginning at 2nd level, you prepare subtle supernatural reinforcements woven directly into your clothing, armor, and accessories.

During your daily preparations, you can prepare a limited number of **tailored defenses**. A tailored defense represents reinforced seams, layered cloth, hidden weights, or protective treatments that remain effective until your next daily preparations.

Tailored defenses are not items and cannot be removed, transferred, or stolen.

### Tailored Defense Slots

You can prepare a limited number of tailored defenses at a time.

You gain a number of Tailored Defense Slots equal to 1 + your proficiency bonus in your Combat Seamstress class DC.

You can prepare the same tailored defense more than once only if it explicitly allows it.

### Using Tailored Defenses

Unless otherwise stated, tailored defenses apply only to you.

Some tailored defenses provide passive benefits. Others grant a single-use or limited-use effect that is expended when triggered. Once expended, a tailored defense provides no further benefit until your next daily preparations.

Starting at 6th level, you can prepare tailored defenses for willing allies. Choose the ally during your daily preparations; the defense functions only while that ally wears or carries the tailored garment or accessory.

|

